# A/B Testing (controlled experiment)
############################################################################################
#
############################################################################################
# Application of A/B testing:
    # e.g. Amazon could use A/B testing to test whether different price is leading to more profit, whether different webside design is getting more customers,
        # whether different recommendation algorithm lead to better clicks, etc.
    # e.g. Netflix could test whether new algorithm is recommending more relevant videos, whether a website design is better, etc.
############################################################################################
# Designing of A/B testing:
    # sample_size >= 16 * sigma ^2 / delta ^ 2
    # delta == minimum detectable effect (e.g. 0.1% increase in revenue)
    # number_of_days >= 14 and or number_of_days = sample_size / number_of_users 

